title: Patricia Breen Claude Monet Sandvika, Norway Santa Ornament
description:
Ornament developed from Claude Monet’s Sandvika, Norway, 1895, from the Art Institute of Chicago’s collection.

A classic rosy-cheeked St. Nick made of hand-painted and hand-silvered mouth-blown glass shows the snowy scene in Monet's Sandvika, Norway, 1895, inside his sparkle trimmed coat. A limited-edition piece created by artist Patricia Breen in her studio in Poland.

  • Dimensions: 6.49 x 3.14 x 3.13 in.
  • Materials: Glass
  • Hand painted, silvered.
  • Made in Poland
